      id: 'facelift',
      title: 'Facelift (Rhytidectomy)',
      humorLevel: 'low',
      content: `The facelift addresses the lower two-thirds of the face—jowls, nasolabial folds, and jawline definition.

**What It Does:**
- Lifts and tightens facial tissues
- Repositions descended fat pads
- Removes excess skin
- Defines jawline
- Reduces nasolabial folds

**Types:**

**Full/Traditional Facelift**
- Incisions around ear, into hairline
- Addresses all lower face concerns
- SMAS layer tightening (muscle/tissue layer)
- Most dramatic, longest-lasting results
- Recovery: 2-4 weeks major, 3-6 months full

**Mini/Limited Facelift**
- Shorter incisions
- Less extensive tissue work
- Good for early jowling
- Less downtime (1-2 weeks major)
- Results less dramatic, may not last as long

**Deep Plane Facelift**
- Goes deeper than SMAS layer
- More natural, long-lasting results
- Requires highly skilled surgeon
- Similar recovery to traditional

**Recovery:**
| Timeframe | Expect |
|-----------|--------|
| Days 1-3 | Significant swelling, bruising |
| Week 1 | Major swelling subsiding |
| Week 2 | Sutures/staples out |
| Week 3-4 | Return to work possible |
| Month 2-3 | Most swelling resolved |
| Month 6-12 | Final result |

**Results Last:** 7-15 years depending on technique, genetics, lifestyle`,
